  "title": "Senior / Respiratory Therapist",
  "description": "<p>The incumbent shall be responsible to :</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide respiratory care services to patients with cardio-respiratory diseases and disorders by assessing patient's respiratory status, recommending, implementing and evaluating appropriate therapy</li>\n  <li>Plans, evaluates and implements diagnostic and therapeutic respiratory care services to aid and assist the physician in the diagnosis and management of patients</li>\n  <li>Responsible for the inventory, care and maintenance of respiratory related equipment and assists with the general functions involving the Respiratory Therapy Department</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree from a recognised school of Respiratory Therapy, preferably with Registration for Respiratory Therapists (Certification Exam)</li>\n  <li>Certifications in Advanced Cardiac Life Support (ACLS) and Basic Cardiac Life Support (BCLS) is preferred</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of adult multi-disciplinary critical care experience</li>\n  <li>Ability to communicate effectively with patients and other healthcare workers and demonstrate a willingness to take on challenges, innovative and well-motivated to apply and share knowledge and skills</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and be part of a team that is committed to providing quality, cost-effective and specialised care to our patients</li>\n</ul>",
